title="Relation"
addr="jms-00I7"
type="local">relation</fr:link> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> to <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is nothing more than a subset of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex>. By the axiom of extensionality, two subsets of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[A\times  B]]></fr:tex> are equal if and only if they contain precisely the same elements.</fr:p>
